[Makefile.gz](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/10094494/Makefile.gz)
[test.sv.gz](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/10094495/test.sv.gz)

Example:
```sv
module fifo(
	input	logic		clk,
	input	logic		rstn,

	input	logic		wr_en,
	input	logic	[7:0]	wdata,
	input	logic		rd_en,
	output	logic	[7:0]	rdata,

	output	logic		empty,
	output	logic		full
);

	logic	[7:0]	mem_arr	[16];
	logic	[3:0]	rd_ptr;
	logic	[3:0]	wr_ptr;
	logic	[4:0]	count;

	always @(posedge clk) begin
		if (wr_en) begin
			$display("Write: %d @%d", wdata, wr_ptr);
			mem_arr[wr_ptr]	<= #0.2 wdata;
		end
	end

	always @(posedge clk or negedge rstn) begin
	if (~rstn) begin
		rd_ptr	<= 'd0;
		wr_ptr	<= 'd0;
		count	<= 'd0;
	end else begin
		rd_ptr	<= #0.2 rd_ptr + rd_en;
		wr_ptr	<= #0.2 wr_ptr + wr_en;
		count	<= #0.2 count + wr_en - rd_en;
	end
	end

	always_comb begin
		rdata	= mem_arr[rd_ptr];
		empty	= (count == 0)? 1'b1: 1'b0;
		full	= (count == 16)? 1'b1: 1'b0;
	end
endmodule
```
A pretty simple FIFO design. When I try to assign to the memory array element with `mem_arr[wr_ptr] <= #0.2 wdata` things don't work. Nothing get's written the the memory location. However if I remove  the `#0.2`  delay things work exactly  as expected. A full example is attached along with the makefile and my logs.
[test.no_delay.log.gz](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/10094524/test.no_delay.log.gz)
[test.with_delay.log.gz](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/10094525/test.with_delay.log.gz)


Verilator Version: Verilator 5.002 2022-10-29 rev UNKNOWN.REV
OS: ArchLinux
May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself? Sure...
